## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="141bc-109"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> peut se bloquer lorsqu’il existe une transaction ambiante et <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Complete%2A> est appelée et par la suite la transaction est restaurée.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="141bc-109"><xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> may hang when there is an ambient transaction and <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Complete%2A> is called and afterwards the transaction is rolled back.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="141bc-110">Si <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> est appelée avant la fin de rollback transaction, une condition de concurrence se produira, à l’origine de l’appel à <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> ne répond plus.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="141bc-110">If <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> is called prior to the transaction rollback completing, a race condition will exist, causing the call to <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext.Abandon%2A> to hang.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="141bc-111">Cela peut être illustrée par l’exemple de pseudo-code suivant</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="141bc-111">This can be illustrated by the following pseudo-code example</span></span>  
  
```  
using (TransactionScope ts = new TransactionScope())   
{  
   try  
   {  
       rc.Complete();  
      ...  
   }  
   Catch (Exception)   
   {  
      rc.Abandon()  
   }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="141bc-112">Ce n’est pas le modèle recommandé pour travailler avec <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="141bc-112">This is not the recommended pattern for working with <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.ReceiveContext>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="141bc-113">Au lieu de cela, le bloc try/catch doit être placé en dehors de l’étendue de transaction.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="141bc-113">Instead the try/catch block should be placed outside of the transaction scope.</span></span>

